SIMPLE: poppet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poppet
<hw>Pop"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>See
<er>Puppet</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>One of certain upright timbers on
the bilge ways, used to support a vessel in launching.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>An upright support or guide
fastened at the bottom only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>same as <er>poppit</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Poppet head</b></col>, <col><b>Puppet
head</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See <er>Headstock</er>
<sd>(a)</sd>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poppied</ent>⟦br⟧
